{
  "stem": "15962.6",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And somewhere near there, a-- oh, before we arrived to Melk, a, a Russian officer boarded the, the ship, the boat and took over the transport from the Americans.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He was an officer that looked like a vagabond with a blanket around him and dirty boots and tattered uniform.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Whereas the American soldier-- and he wasn't even an officer-- was in perfectly pressed uniform and looked impeccable.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] ship then docked in Melk.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we were asked to leave the ship and were escorted back to the camp that we left three months earlier.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And this was a terrible shock to us because this, the memories of the conditions that prevailed there could not be easily erased.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were literally afraid that we were now interned by the Russians, and maybe we are no better off than we were before.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] After a day or two in this camp, we were taken by train to a town called Wiener Neustadt.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It's not Vienna.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It's a, it's a town about 50 kilometers southwest of Vienna.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We had to zigzag because the track was-- bridges were down, and the track was destroyed in many places.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And when we arrived there, the railway station was-- everything, the whole town, was in ruin, completely bombed out.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The Russian soldiers who took care of us had nothing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They were, they were riding on these Studebaker trucks that the Americans gave the Russian army.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They had to fend for themselves for food.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They had to, to steal or loot everything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They were not supplied with anything except a, a rifle and, and ammunition and a blanket.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
